“Upon his swearing-in on May 29, 2019, Buhari merely took the oaths of office and allegiance, inspected the guards’ brigade, jumped into his convoy and left.” And thus, Buhari became the first leader since October 1, 1960, not deliver speech upon inauguration, either for first or second term. M y Take:
His supporters will rationalise this and dismiss any reservation genuinely raised by Nigerians. They will soon tell you: “No big deal. He was not under any obligation to deliver speech. Besides, the President is keeping his good plans for Nigerians close to his chest.” Asira oja ni baba yen. And his supporters who can defend even daylight robbery? Asigbe omokomo ni woodu… Source: Facebook